{"questionId":"27748","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is defined by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The region enclosed by the curve <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math>, the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis and the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-axis is rotated through&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math> radians about the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis to form a solid of revolution.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the volume of this solid.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-intercept is at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>33</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use formula for volume of revolution&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for an integral involving <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math>. Condone use of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math> and incorrect or absent limits.</p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><munderover><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></munderover><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> This <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em> can be awarded if the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>d</mtext><mi>x</mi></math> is omitted.</p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>164</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>849</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>165</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27748","referenceCode":"22N.2.AHL.TZ0.11c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the volume of this solid.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.17—Areas under curve onto y-axis, volume of revolution (about x and y axes)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}